.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/mick-jagger-keith-richards-rilling-stones-2000x1270-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/mick-jagger-keith-richards-rilling-stones-2000x1270-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/mick-jagger-keith-richards-rilling-stones-2000x1270-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/mick-jagger-keith-richards-rilling-stones-2000x1270-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/mick-jagger-keith-richards-rilling-stones-2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>解释了他们期待已久的新专辑“Hackney Diamonds”标题背后的含义。观看上面的完整新闻发布会。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">这支传奇乐队昨天（9 月 6 日）宣布了他们的第 24 张录音室唱片</a>，并分享了其主打单曲“Angry”。继 2005 年的<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-the-rolling-stones-7763-312997">《A Bigger Bang》</a>之后，这将是他们 18 年来首张原创音乐合集。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/rolling-stone-songs-10-best-2263181">滚石乐队 – 他们最好的 10 首歌曲</a></strong></li></ul><p>在哈克尼帝国举行的现场新闻发布会上，主持人吉米·法伦询问<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mick-jagger">米克·贾格尔</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/keith-richards">基思·理查兹</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ronnie-wood">罗尼·伍德</a>即将发行的专辑的标题对他们意味着什么。</p><p>理查兹回应道：“它被称为‘Hackney Diamonds’，因为我们在游戏中不断提出想法，我们从‘Hit And Run’变成了‘Smash And Grab’。不知何故，我们想出了“哈克尼钻石”，它就像两者的变体。”</p><p>他补充道：“而且，这是一支伦敦乐队。”</p><p>法伦接着问“哈克尼钻石”是否是“一种俚语”，贾格尔回答说：“是的，这就像周六晚上在哈克尼你的挡风玻璃被打破，所有的碎片都流到了街上...... ‘哈克尼钻石’。” </p><figure id="attachment_3494162" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3494162" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3494162" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270.jpg" alt="滚石乐队" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2023_therollingstones_markseliger_2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3494162" class="wp-caption-text">滚石乐队 图片来源：Mark Seliger</figcaption></figure><p>在<em>《NME》</em>参加的直播会议的其他地方，滚石乐队透露， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-reveal-charlie-watts-appears-on-two-tracks-of-new-album-hackney-diamonds-3494170">《Hackney Diamonds》中的两首歌是由他们已故鼓手查理·瓦茨 (Charlie Watts) 演唱的</a>。这两首歌曲名为“Mess It Up”和“Live By The Sword”，均于 2019 年录制。</p><p>这张专辑在多个地点录制，包括洛杉矶的 Henson Recording Studios、伦敦的 Metropolis Studios、巴哈马的 Sanctuary Studios、Electric Lady Studios 和纽约的 The Hit Factory/Germano Studios。</p><p> “我不想自大，但如果我们不是真的喜欢这张专辑，我们就不会发行它，”贾格尔在昨天的活动中解释道。 “我们说我们必须制作一张我们真正爱自己的唱片。</p><p> “我们对此非常满意。我们并不自以为是，但希望大家喜欢。”</p><p> “Hackney Diamonds” 将于 10 月 20 日以各种格式发布 -<a href="https://therollingstones.lnk.to/HackneyDiamondsPR" target="_blank" rel="noopener">您可以在此处预订/预保存</a>。</p><p>滚石乐队的最新专辑于 2016 年以蓝调翻唱唱片<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/rolling-stones-blue-lonesome-1882686#:~:text=These%2012%20tracks%20were%20recorded,but%20not%20wanting%20for%20thrills.">《Blue &amp; Lonesome》</a>的形式推出。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-explain-meaning-of-new-hackney-diamonds-album-name-3494480">滚石乐队解释新专辑“Hackney Diamonds”名称含义的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
